    diagnostics: ["Serum creatine kinase (CK): massively elevated (10-100x normal, often >10,000 IU/L) — earliest laboratory finding, elevated from birth","Genetic testing for dystrophin gene mutations: deletion/duplication analysis (MLPA) identifies 65-70% of mutations; sequencing for point mutations if MLPA negative","Muscle biopsy with immunohistochemistry: absent dystrophin staining on Western blot confirms diagnosis (rarely needed now with genetic testing)","Electromyography (EMG): myopathic pattern with short-duration, low-amplitude, polyphasic potentials","Echocardiography: baseline and annual to monitor for dilated cardiomyopathy (develops in nearly all patients by age 18)","Pulmonary function tests (spirometry): annual FVC monitoring — progressive decline indicates respiratory muscle weakness","Cardiac MRI with gadolinium enhancement to detect early myocardial fibrosis before echocardiographic changes"],
    management: ["Corticosteroids (prednisone or deflazacort): only proven therapy to slow disease progression — extends ambulation by 2-5 years and delays cardiomyopathy onset","Physical therapy and regular stretching to prevent contractures and maintain range of motion","Cardiac management: ACE inhibitors or ARBs initiated by age 10 (or at first sign of cardiac dysfunction) to delay cardiomyopathy progression","Respiratory support: nocturnal BiPAP when FVC declines below 50% predicted, cough-assist devices for airway clearance","Scoliosis management: spinal bracing and surgical fixation (posterior spinal fusion) when Cobb angle exceeds 20-30 degrees","Gene-targeted therapies: exon-skipping antisense oligonucleotides (eteplirsen, golodirsen) for specific deletions amenable to exon skipping","Annual influenza and pneumococcal vaccinations; aggressive treatment of respiratory infections to prevent pneumonia"],
    nursingActions: ["Assess motor function using standardized tools (6-minute walk test, timed function tests) at each visit to track disease progression","Monitor for signs of respiratory compromise: decreased breath sounds, weak cough, morning headaches, daytime somnolence (hypoventilation)","Perform cardiac assessment at each encounter: auscultate for S3 gallop, assess for peripheral edema and JVD indicating heart failure","Monitor for corticosteroid side effects: weight gain (Cushingoid features), hyperglycemia, behavior changes, cataracts, osteoporosis, growth suppression","Implement fall prevention strategies and assess home safety — wheelchair accessibility, adaptive equipment, bathroom modifications","Provide psychosocial support for child and family: address grief, connect with support organizations (MDA), facilitate school accommodations (IEP/504 plan)","Educate family on emergency preparedness: avoid succinylcholine and volatile anesthetics (malignant hyperthermia risk), carry medical alert identification"],
